-- Taiwan Stocks: Acer, Cathay Financial Holding, Evergreen Marine
-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 2012-03-13T06:26:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-13/taiwan-stocks-acer-cathay-financial-holding-evergreen-marine.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Taiwan trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The benchmark Taiex Index rose 1.3 percent to 8,031.51, the
most since Feb. 29.  Acer Inc. (2353)  (2353 TT) gained 1.9 percent to NT$43, the
biggest advance since March 9. The world’s fourth-largest
computer maker said February sales rose 34 percent from a year
earlier to NT$37.5 billion.  Cathay Financial Holding Co. (2882)  (2882 TT) surged 6.9 percent
to NT$34.90, the steepest increase since Dec. 23. The island’s
largest financial services company is in talks with “several”
Chinese banks about investments, Alan Lee, a spokesman for the
company said today, declining to name the Chinese lenders it is
in talks with.  Evergreen Marine Corp. (2603)  (2603 TT), part of Asia’s second-
largest container shipping line, gained 0.5 percent to NT$20.50.
The company, along with Hanjin Shipping Co. and China Cosco
Holdings Co., will start joint services on the Asia-Europe trade
in April.  To contact the reporter on this story:
